President Cyril Ramaphosa arriving at the Sefako Makgatho Presidential Guesthouse in Tshwane ahead of the swearing in ceremony. JOHANNESBURG - New members of Cabinet have officially been sworn in by Chief Justice Mogoeng Mogoeng at the Sefako Makgatho presidential guesthouse in Pretoria. LIVESTREAM: New Ministers sworn in Ramaphosa announced a trimmer, female-dominated cabinet on Wednesday night, which also came with a few surprises including the appointment of Good leader Patricia de Lille. Meanwhile, the rand continues to strengthen off the back of last night's big reveal. Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs Minister Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma. Basic Education Minister Angie Motshekga. President Cyril Ramaphosa congratulates Deputy President David Mabuza shortly after being sworn-in by the Chief Justice Mogoeng Mogoeng. Chief Justice Mogoeng Mogoeng swearing-in newly appointed Minister Fikile Mbalula. Chief Justice Mogoeng Mogoeng swearing-in newly appointed Minister of Environment, Forestry and Fisheries Barbara Creecy. Mineral Resources and Mining Minister Gwede Mantashe being sworn in by Chief Justice Mogoeng Mogoeng. Chief Justice Mogoeng Mogoeng swearing-in newly appointed Minister Bheki Cele. Public Enterprises Minister Pravin Gordhan being sworn in by Chief Justice Mogoeng Mogoeng at the Sefako Makgatho presidential guesthouse on Thursday. Communications Minister Stella Ndabeni-Abrahams.